						               													<description>With this adventure booklet you can experience another exciting adventure of Robin Hood and his companions. It plays around the same time as chapter 4. The story of the adventure plays independently of the others and therefore no prior knowledge of other chapters is necessary.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Since new elements and tiles from later adventures have been added, it is recommended that you have already played the basic game. All outlaws already have their own special abilities. The functions for new items can be found on the following page. No prior knowledge of this adventure is required.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There was a great uproar in the camp as the village was overrun by the sheriff's guards raided, the forge burned and Father Egbert had been taken prisoner. Robin, John and Will talked about what to do next. But Marian was still deep in thought and firmly convinced of the name to have heard Alatar before. This man had created the curse and this calamity brought about them. Then she saw the smith's wife sitting on the forest floor, crying.&amp;#10;But there were far more important things to think about than the past. Marian was blown away torn. What should she do?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
